<HEAD>Major Drug Bust Nets 183 Pounds of Heroin</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Law enforcement agents arrested four people and
seized 183 pounds of nearly pure heroin from Hong Kong, authorities
said.
   The drugs seized Wednesday had a street value in the hundreds of
millions of dollars, authorities said. The drugs were tracked from
Logan International Airport, where they were discovered two weeks
ago, hidden under machine parts, authorities said.
   Federal and local agents trailed the shipment to a commercial
building in south Boston where it was seized, according to a police
official who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   Officials refused to identify the four arrested Wednesday.
   Ed Callanan, a spokesman for the U.S. Customs Service in Boston,
confirmed the amount and quality heroin seized, but refused to
elaborate.
   U.S. Attorney Frank L. MacNamara said he could not comment on
the arrest.
   ``We're doing our best to complete a mission and when I'm able
to comment officially I will do so,'' MacNamara said.
