<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     09-08 0330</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0339</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Smoke in the West, Rain Over Florida</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Smoke from Western forest fires darkened skies over northern
Wyoming and south central Montana today and showers fell in
northeast Florida, but the weather was fair in much of the rest of
the nation.
   Skies were cloudy over the central Plains.
   A low-temperature record for Sept. 7 was set before midnight
Wednesday in Monroe, La., where it was 54 degrees, 5 degrees lower
than the 1950 mark.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from the
central Atlantic Coast to central Florida and sunny skies over the
rest of the nation, with strong, gusty winds from the upper
Mississippi Valley to the northern Rockies.
   High temperatures were predicted in the 60s in North Dakota, the
70s from New England to New Jersey, the Applachians, the Ohio
Valley, the Great Lakes, the northern Plains, the northern Rockies
and Washington state; the 90s in the southern half of the Plains,
and from southern Oregon to Nevada; near 110 degrees in the desert
Southwest; and in the 80s around the rest of the country.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 39
degrees at Havre, Mont., to 89 degrees at Blythe, Calif.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 61 fair; Boston 57 fair; Buffalo 50 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 65 cloudy; Cincinnati 52 fair; Cleveland 50 fair;
Detroit 51 fair; Miami 83 fair; New York 61 fair; Philadelphia 53
fair; Pittsburgh 47 fair; Portland, Maine 48 fair; Washington 55
fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 57 windy; Chicago 58 fair; Denver 60 fair;
Des Moines 64 partly cloudy; Indianapolis 48 fair; Kansas City 67
fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 65 cloudy; Nashville 62 fair; New
Orleans 70 fair; St. Louis 59 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 62 fair; Anchorage 47 cloudy; Las Vegas 82
fair; Los Angeles 68 cloudy; Phoenix 85 fair; Salt Lake City 59
fair; San Diego 67 cloudy; San Francisco 54 fair; Seattle 55 fair.
