<HEAD>Truck-Van Collision Leaves Two Dead, 12 Injured</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS first and last grafs to UPDATE with second death</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A van carrying a group of Mexicans from
Tijuana to Los Angeles overturned and burst into flames after being
struck by a truck, leaving two dead and 12 others injured,
authorities said.
   The crash occurred Wednesday on Interstate 5 nearly 20 miles
north of San Diego.
   ``The van was apparently moving very slowly and the truck forced
the van into the guard rail,'' said California Highway Patrol
spokeswoman Katie Nielsen.
   The dead and injured were aboard the van, she said. The driver
of the truck fled on foot and was being sought, she added.
   Another spokeswoman who refused to be identified said some
others who were in the van also fled the scene. It was not clear if
the van's driver fled or was a casualty, she added.
   One woman died at the scene from severe burns, Ms. Nielsen said.
Another woman died of burns and trauma at University of California
at San Diego's Medical Center, said a nursing supervisor who
declined to give her name. Twelve others were taken to hospitals
and four were in serious condition with burns, officials said.
