<HEAD>Former Police Captain Sentenced In Sex Abuse Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former police captain who had himself
castrated in a bid for leniency has been sentenced to 15 years in
prison for having sex with boys.
   Sidney Elijah Pourciau, 62, pleaded guilty in April to
aggravated crime against nature in cases involving four boys.
   Judge Mike Ponder sentenced Pourciau on Wednesday to the maximum
of 15 years on each of four counts and ordered the terms to be
served concurrently.
   Pourciau, who retired in 1985 after 32 years on the Baton Rouge
force, was arrested in 1986 after a parent of an 11-year-old
neighbor complained of sexual abuse. The assaults on boys in the
neighborhood began in 1981, police said.
   Pourciau voluntarily underwent castration in an effort to solve
his sexual problem, a defense attorney said.
   After pronouncing sentence, the judge told Pourciau, ``I think
you've made a sincere effort to rehabilitate yourself from this
problem, this sickness, you have.''
