<HEAD>First Vietnam Vet Becomes National Commander</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The American Legion on Thursday elected
its first national commander who is a veteran of the Vietnam War.
   Legionnaires said the election of H.F. ``Sparky'' Gierke, 45, of
Watford City, N.D., is a way to attract younger veterans to the
world's largest organization of veterans.
   Gierke, a North Dakota Supreme Court justice, was a full-time
military judge in Vietnam. He was discharged in April 1971.
   Gierke, who was not opposed, was elected by acclamation at the
legion's 70th annual convention.
   Gierke succeeds John P. ``Jake'' Comer of Massachusetts.
