<HEAD>Oil Well Explodes In Flames</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ARCOLA, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An oil well exploded in flames early today,
killing at least one person and seriously burning several others,
the sheriff's office said.
   The identity of the well's owner was not immediately available.
   Chuck Reed, a Tangipahoa Parish sheriff's deputy, said the
person killed may have been a teen-ager who had been riding a
motorcycle near the well. The fire was believed to have been
brought under control before noon, Reed said.
