<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Ecuador-PlaneCrash     09-08 0202</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Ecuador-Plane Crash,0207</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Plane Crash Kills 10 In Ecuador</HEAD>
<DATELINE>QUITO, Ecuador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small plane spewing flames and smoke
crashed into a shrimp pond after takeoff Thursday, killing all 10
people aboard, officials and witnesses said.
   The Cesna 421-C crashed about 9 a.m., three minutes after taking
off from the Machala airport on a flight to Quito, 230 miles north,
said government spokesman Cosme Valverde.
   ``The plane was sending smoke and flames from its tail,''
witness Carlos Echevarria said in a radio interview.
   The craft was owned by a small private airline company called
Edsan. The company and Valverde said all eight passengers and two
crew members were killed.
   Listed as dead are pilot Miguel Garamillo, a co-pilot and six
men passengers, a woman and a child whose age and identity was not
determined, officials said.
   The officials said the craft crashed into ponds on a shrimp
farm, but said they did not know the cause of the accident. The
company said investigators were sent to the crash site.
   In the last major plane crash in Ecuador, 10 top air force
officials and an Israeli military attache were killed June 3 when
their plane crashed into a mountain near Quito.
