<HEAD>People in the News</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS first item, datelined Chicago, to UPDATE with Thursday
performance also canceled.</NOTE>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lily Tomlin's bag-lady persona, Trudy, was in the
middle of croaking out a monologue when Ms. Tomlin broke through to
tell a startled opening-night crowd, ``I'm going to have to stop
here.''
   Ms. Tomlin said she had been out sailing on Lake Michigan and as
a result was losing her voice at the first performance here Tuesday
of her one-woman show, ``The Search for Signs of Intelligent Life
in the Universe.''
   Ms. Tomlin tried to continue Tuesday, after suggesting critics
leave the theater. But after an off-stage consultation, she told
the audience she had decided not to go on because she was ``giving
a mediocre performance and compromising the material. It's not fair
to you.''
