<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Production,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
189,561 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
215,327, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 174,162 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 118,885 cars this week,
compared with 136,771 a week ago and 108,245 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 70,676,
compared with last week's 78,556 and last year's 65,917.
   Canadian automakers were to build 16,509 cars this week, down
from 18,013 a week ago but up from last year's 12,230.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 17,343,
compared with 18,348 a week ago and 13,866 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
